other_tests.findings: Alkaline phosphatase levels dropped within the normal range and remained at normal levels for 5 months after the final dose of denosumab.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After denosumab treatment, bone turnover markers TSAP, BAP, TRAP5b, and NTX levels started to increase again after 6 weeks.

other_tests.findings: Severe hypocalcemia developed after the first injection of denosumab, with ionized calcium levels dropping to 0.71 mmol/L.
other_tests.changes_over_time: No hypocalcemia was observed after the second dose of denosumab.

other_tests.findings: Regular ECG readings showed no abnormalities during treatment.
Homozygous mutation in the osteoprotegerin gene TNFRSF11B was identified.
Elevated PTH levels were noted after the first injection of denosumab.
